The Art-Makers of Nineteenth-Century America
Atheneum | 1970 | ISBN: N/A | English | 536 pages | PDF | 54.4 MB

It took nerve and a certain gall to set out to be an art-maker in America in the nineteenth century," Russell Lynes writes at the beginning of this critical narrative of painters, sculptors, architects and designers in the lively, tough years when America was growing up
